    public final class FieldHashMap<K,V>
extends FieldMap<K,V>
    An implementation of a HashMap that begins life as mutable but can, at any time, be "frozen" (made immutable). In other words, a wrapper for a HashMap that implements Field.

    Note: HashMap, and consequently FieldHashMap is not thread safe. This is generally not a concern once "frozen" but if the construction process is multi-threaded, consider FieldConcurrentHashMap.

    In the standard case (construction in one thread), FieldHashMap will work well.
